                   Tate
               <interp inst="t17830910-2-person103" type="surname" value="Tate"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17830910-2-person103" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17830910-2-person103" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , is annotation in my hand writing, purporting the sum, which identifies the power of attorney.</p>
               <p>Did you know a man of the name of Tate? - A man of the name of Tate has since applied, and I paid him yesterday morning, the prisoner was taken up for some other offence, and the power was found in his pocket.</p>
               <p>(The Letter of Attorney read.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17830910-2-person104">
                  SAMUEL
                   TATE
